headlines.description: Joe Sherburne had 21 points and 10 rebounds and three seniors had key contributions on Senior Day as UMBC defeated UMass Lowell 83-75 on Saturday to secure 20 wins in back-to-back seasons for the first time at the Division-I level.

Tyler Nelson scored 23 points, Jonathan Kasibabu added 20, including a go-ahead layup with 38 seconds left, and fifth-place Fairfield rallied to beat seventh-place Monmouth 69-66 on Saturday in the Metro Atlantic Athletic Conference regular-season...

Scottie James scored 21 points, 15 after halftime, grabbed seven rebounds and blocked four shots as Liberty dominated inside and clobbered High Point 65-45 on Saturday, pulling even with Panthers in the Big South Conference.
headlines.shortLinkText: James a power in the post, Liberty wallops High Point 65-45

headlines.description: Charles Brown III had 18 points with Shawn Johnson adding 14 with 10 rebounds as Incarnate Word picked up its first Southland Conference victory of the season, beating Texas A&M-Corpus Christi 69-62 on its home floor on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Incarnate Word gets 1st league win of the season 69-62

headlines.description: Steven Whitley scored 14 points with eight rebounds and seven assists and Preston Bungei scored 18 points and Norfolk State beat Maryland-Eastern Shore 74-63 on Saturday.

Jarren Greenwood scored 21 points while dishing out four assists to help McNeese regroup in the second half to beat Houston Baptist 88-79 on Saturday and remain in contention to grab the final spot in the Southland Conference Tournament.
headlines.shortLinkText: McNeese regroups in 2nd half, beats Houston Baptist 88-79

headlines.description: Chris Clemons scored 23 points and distributed nine assists and Damontez Oliver scored 13 and Campbell defeated Presbyterian 72-56 on Saturday to finish in fourth place in the Big South standings.
headlines.shortLinkText: Campbell controls Presbyterian for 72-56 win behind Clemons

headlines.description: Liam O'Reilly made four 3-pointers and scored 24 points and Gardner-Webb defeated Big South champion UNC Asheville 72-61 on Saturday in a regular-season finale.
headlines.shortLinkText: Gardner-Webb beats Big South champ UNC Asheville 72-61

headlines.description: Erick Neal flirted with a triple-double as UT Arlington upset Georgia State 89-81 in Sun Belt Conference action on Saturday afternoon.
headlines.shortLinkText: Neal, Hervey help UT Arlington upset Georgia St. 89-81

headlines.description: Matthew Butler scored 25 points and Tennessee-Martin beat Southeast Missouri State 72-66 on Saturday afternoon in a regular season finale.
headlines.shortLinkText: UT Martin beats SE Missouri State 72-66

headlines.description: Ike Smith scored 25 points with five 3-pointers, Tookie Brown scored all of his 16 points in the second half, and third-place Georgia Southern beat Texas State 81-77 on Saturday to split the season series.
headlines.shortLinkText: Smith scores 25, Georgia Southern beats Texas State 81-77

headlines.description: Nick Garth drained six from long range to total 23 points as Lamar upset Stephen F. Austin 71-66 on Saturday to complete its first season sweep of the Lumberjacks since the 2001-02 campaign.
headlines.shortLinkText: Garth scores 23, Lamar upsets SF Austin to complete sweep

headlines.description: Mike Daum poured in 31 points and snagged 13 rebounds and Tevin King added a double-double of his own to lead South Dakota State to a 97-90 victory over Fort Wayne on Saturday night for its eighth straight win.
headlines.shortLinkText: Daum leads South Dakota State past Fort Wayne 97-90

headlines.description: Travis Charles grabbed a career-high 14 rebounds and scored 16, Joe Cremo scored 24 and Albany repeatedly blunted Maine's attempted rallies for an 89-79 win Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Albany downs Maine 89-79 behind 24 pts from Cremo

headlines.description: Jamaal King scored 26 points and St. Francis of Pennsylvania pulled away in the second half to earn an 80-60 win over Robert Morris Saturday night to claim a second-place finish in the Northeast Conference.
headlines.shortLinkText: St. Francis (PA) pulls away from Robert Morris, 80-60,

headlines.description: Nate Sherwood had 15 points and 10 rebounds and hit all four of his free throws in the final 24 seconds to help Idaho beat Weber State 68-62 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Idaho beats Weber State, moves into 2nd place in Big Sky

headlines.description: Kyle Allman made 8 of 13 from the field, hit 8 of 9 from the free-throw line and finished with 25 points to help Cal State Fullerton beat Long Beach State 81-71 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Allman scores 25 points, CS Fullerton beats Long Beach State

nowFeed.headline:
I followed Grayson Allen closely since his high school days. A fierce  competitor who gave it his all. He never had one issue on or off the court. I called Duke's game last year when Grayson Allen had his tripping incident. Tonight on senior night in a win over North Carolina I loved listening to Maria Taylor's post-game interview with Allen. 
What does Duke mean to you? 
" It means everything to me, it's my love and my passion. " Allen said. 
I call that growing up.
